---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import leadVehicle250ps from '../assets/LeadVehicle_250ps.mp4';
import leadVehicle5ns from '../assets/LeadVehicle_5ns.mp4';
import pedestrian250ps from '../assets/Pedestrian_250ps.mp4';
import pedestrian5ns from '../assets/Pedestrian_5ns.mp4';
import sharcCarlaDiagram from '../assets/sharc-carla diagram.png';
import turning250ps from '../assets/Turning_250ps.mp4';
import turning5ns from '../assets/Turning_5ns.mp4';

const authors = [
	{ name: 'Shengmin Liu', affiliation: 'University of California, Berkeley' },
	{ name: 'Yash Mathur', affiliation: 'University of California, Berkeley' },
	{ name: 'Tyler Brady', affiliation: 'University of California, Berkeley' },
	{ name: 'Malavikha Sudarshan', affiliation: 'University of California, Berkeley' },
	{ name: 'Yasin Sonmez', affiliation: 'University of California, Berkeley' },
	{ name: 'Murat Arcak', affiliation: 'University of California, Berkeley' },
];

const projectLinks = [
	{ label: 'Paper', href: '#' },
	{ label: 'Code', href: '#' },
	{ label: 'Poster', href: '#' },
	{ label: 'Demo Video', href: '#' },
];

const highlights = [
	'Integrates the SHARC processor and control simulator with CARLA driving environments.',
	'Models perception, planning, and control latency instead of assuming instantaneous computation.',
	'Sets up safety-critical experiments where small delays measurably change driving outcomes.',
];

const scenarios = [
	{
		title: 'Intersection Right-Turn',
		description:
			'Comparison between high-frequency and low-frequency execution during a right turn through an intersection.',
		highVideo: turning250ps,
		lowVideo: turning5ns,
	},
	{
		title: 'Lead Vehicle Stop',
		description:
			'Front vehicle braking scenario showing how execution latency changes following and stopping behavior.',
		highVideo: leadVehicle250ps,
		lowVideo: leadVehicle5ns,
	},
	{
		title: 'Pedestrian Crossing',
		description:
			'Pedestrian crossing rollout highlighting how delayed computation affects reaction timing near the crosswalk.',
		highVideo: pedestrian250ps,
		lowVideo: pedestrian5ns,
	},
];

const bibtex = String.raw`@misc{sharcdrive2026,
  title        = {SHARC-Drive: Hardware-Aware Driving Simulation with SHARC and CARLA},
  author       = {Your Capstone Team},
  year         = {2026},
  note         = {Project page boilerplate}
}`;
---

<Layout
	title="SHARC-Drive | SHARC CARLA"
	description="SHARC-Drive integrates SHARC with CARLA to study how processor-level computation latency affects autonomous driving performance."
>
	<main class="mx-auto max-w-5xl px-6 py-10 sm:px-8">
		<section class="mx-auto max-w-4xl text-center">
			<h1 class="text-4xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-zinc-950 sm:text-5xl">
				SHARC-Drive
			</h1>
			<p class="mt-4 text-lg text-zinc-700">
				Hardware-aware driving simulation with SHARC and CARLA
			</p>
			<div class="mt-6 flex flex-wrap justify-center gap-x-6 gap-y-3 text-[15px] text-zinc-700">
				{
					authors.map((author) => (
						<p>
							<span class="font-medium text-zinc-900">{author.name}</span>
							<span class="text-zinc-500"> · {author.affiliation}</span>
						</p>
					))
				}
			</div>
			<div class="mt-6 flex flex-wrap justify-center gap-3">
				{
					projectLinks.map((link) => (
						<a
							class="rounded-md border border-zinc-300 px-4 py-2 text-sm text-zinc-800 transition hover:bg-zinc-50"
							href={link.href}
						>
							{link.label}
						</a>
					))
				}
			</div>
		</section>

		<section class="mx-auto mt-10 max-w-4xl">
			<div class="overflow-hidden rounded-lg border border-zinc-300 bg-zinc-50">
				<div class="flex aspect-[16/9] items-center justify-center text-sm text-zinc-500">
					Teaser image, system diagram, or short demo video
				</div>
			</div>
			<p class="mt-3 text-center text-sm text-zinc-600">
				Replace this placeholder with the main SHARC-CARLA figure or a short demonstration clip.
			</p>
		</section>

		<section id="overview" class="mx-auto mt-14 max-w-4xl">
			<h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-zinc-950">Abstract</h2>
			<p class="mt-4 leading-8 text-zinc-700">
				In autonomous driving, control algorithms ranging from PID to nonlinear
				model predictive control (NMPC) must be executed within a strict sample
				period on embedded processors whose computational resources vary widely.
				The computation time depends on the microarchitecture, including clock
				speed, cache size, and pipeline depth, and interacts with the
				controller's algorithmic complexity in ways that are difficult to predict
				analytically. This paper presents a co-simulation framework coupling
				SHARC (Simulator for Hardware Architecture and Real-time Control) with
				the CARLA driving simulator, enabling systematic evaluation of how
				hardware and controller design choices jointly affect closed-loop safety.
			</p>
			<p class="mt-4 leading-8 text-zinc-700">
				<strong class="font-semibold text-zinc-900">Index Terms</strong>:
				Hardware-software co-design, autonomous driving, model predictive
				control, computational delay, microarchitecture simulation.
			</p>
		</section>

		<section class="mx-auto mt-12 max-w-4xl">
			<h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-zinc-950">Overview</h2>
			<p class="mt-4 leading-8 text-zinc-700">
				The main goal is to move beyond idealized driving simulation and evaluate autonomous policies under realistic compute constraints. Instead of assuming that perception, planning, and control complete instantly, SHARC-Drive makes execution delay part of the simulation.
			</p>
			<ul class="mt-5 list-disc space-y-2 pl-6 leading-8 text-zinc-700">
				{
					highlights.map((highlight) => (
						<li>{highlight}</li>
					))
				}
			</ul>
		</section>

		<section class="mx-auto mt-12 max-w-4xl">
			<h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-zinc-950">Method Overview</h2>
			<div class="mt-5 overflow-hidden rounded-lg border border-zinc-300 bg-zinc-50">
				<img
					class="w-full"
					src={sharcCarlaDiagram.src}
					width={sharcCarlaDiagram.width}
					height={sharcCarlaDiagram.height}
					alt="SHARC-CARLA system architecture diagram"
				/>
			</div>
			<div class="mt-5 space-y-4 text-base leading-8 text-zinc-700">
				<p>
					<strong class="font-semibold text-zinc-900">CARLA</strong> provides
					high-fidelity driving environments and sensor data, enabling simulation of
					various scenarios under <strong class="font-semibold text-zinc-900"
						>deterministic, reproducible conditions</strong
					>. This makes it possible to evaluate autonomous behavior consistently
					across repeated runs while varying scenario setup, traffic, and
					environmental context.
				</p>
				<p>
					<strong class="font-semibold text-zinc-900">SHARC</strong> models
					multiple processor architectures to evaluate
					<strong class="font-semibold text-zinc-900"
						>control execution performance across hardware</strong
					>. Rather than assuming perception, planning, and control complete
					instantly, it captures how processor-level timing and execution delay can
					vary depending on the underlying compute platform.
				</p>
				<p>
					<strong class="font-semibold text-zinc-900"
						>Integrating both in a closed loop</strong
					>, we track <strong class="font-semibold text-zinc-900"
						>control algorithm performance</strong
					> of the ego vehicle under <strong class="font-semibold text-zinc-900"
						>hardware constraints</strong
					>. This lets us study not only what decision the controller makes, but
					whether that decision is produced in time to remain safe in
					latency-sensitive driving scenarios.
				</p>
			</div>
		</section>

		<section id="scenarios" class="mx-auto mt-12 max-w-4xl">
			<h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-zinc-950">Qualitative Comparisons</h2>
			<p class="mt-4 leading-8 text-zinc-700">
				Each scenario is shown at the two latency extremes currently included in the dataset: high-frequency execution at 250 ps clock period (4 GHz) and low-frequency execution at 5 ns clock period (200 MHz).
			</p>
			<div class="mt-6 hidden grid-cols-[minmax(0,1.1fr)_minmax(0,1fr)_minmax(0,1fr)] gap-4 text-center text-sm font-medium text-zinc-700 md:grid">
				<div></div>
				<div>High Frequency: 250 ps / 4 GHz</div>
				<div>Low Frequency: 5 ns / 200 MHz</div>
			</div>
			<div class="mt-4 space-y-10">
				{
					scenarios.map((scenario) => (
						<div class="border-t border-zinc-200 pt-6 first:border-t-0 first:pt-0">
							<div class="md:grid md:grid-cols-[minmax(0,1.1fr)_minmax(0,1fr)_minmax(0,1fr)] md:gap-4">
								<div class="md:pr-4">
									<h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-zinc-950">{scenario.title}</h3>
									<p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-7 text-zinc-700">{scenario.description}</p>
								</div>
								<div class="mt-4 md:mt-0">
									<p class="mb-2 text-sm font-medium text-zinc-700 md:hidden">
										High Frequency: 250 ps / 4 GHz
									</p>
									<div class="overflow-hidden rounded-lg border border-zinc-300 bg-black">
										<video
											class="aspect-video w-full"
											src={scenario.highVideo}
											autoplay
											muted
											loop
											playsinline
											controls
										/>
									</div>
								</div>
								<div class="mt-4 md:mt-0">
									<p class="mb-2 text-sm font-medium text-zinc-700 md:hidden">
										Low Frequency: 5 ns / 200 MHz
									</p>
									<div class="overflow-hidden rounded-lg border border-zinc-300 bg-black">
										<video
											class="aspect-video w-full"
											src={scenario.lowVideo}
											autoplay
											muted
											loop
											playsinline
											controls
										/>
									</div>
								</div>
							</div>
						</div>
					))
				}
			</div>
		</section>

		<section id="results" class="mx-auto mt-12 max-w-4xl">
			<h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-zinc-950">Performance Results</h2>
			<div class="mt-5 overflow-hidden rounded-lg border border-zinc-300 bg-zinc-50">
				<div class="flex aspect-[16/9] items-center justify-center text-sm text-zinc-500">
					Performance plot or results figure placeholder
				</div>
			</div>
			<ul class="mt-5 list-disc space-y-2 pl-6 leading-8 text-zinc-700">
				<li>Collision rate under varying processor and scheduling configurations</li>
				<li>Reaction-time shift between nominal and latency-aware simulations</li>
				<li>Control smoothness and braking aggressiveness under delay</li>
				<li>Scenario-level analysis of unsafe delayed actions</li>
			</ul>
		</section>

		<section id="details" class="mx-auto mt-12 max-w-4xl pb-8">
			<h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-zinc-950">BibTeX</h2>
			<pre class="mt-4 overflow-x-auto rounded-lg border border-zinc-300 bg-zinc-50 p-4 text-sm leading-7 text-zinc-700"><code>{bibtex}</code></pre>
		</section>
	</main>
</Layout>
